---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial standards"
  description="How BES3 protects clarity, independence and accuracy."
>
  <section class="page-hero shell">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">OUR STANDARD</p><h1>Independence is a process.</h1></div><p
      class="lede"
    >
      The same questions apply to every ingredient, product category and brand feature.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="section reading-width article-body">
    <h2>Sources before slogans</h2><p>
      We prefer primary research, systematic reviews, professional guidance and official product
      information for facts such as ingredients, directions and availability.
    </p>
    <h2>Claims and evidence stay separate</h2><p>
      Brand language is presented as a claim, not as independent proof. We explain what a source can
      support and where it stops.
    </p>
    <h2>No manufactured authority</h2><p>
      We do not invent dermatologists, clinical testing, user results, product trials or personal
      experience. An article is labelled as a guide or claims analysis when the editor has not used
      the product.
    </p>
    <h2>Paid and affiliate work</h2><p>
      Affiliate and sponsored relationships are disclosed. They do not determine headlines,
      conclusions or ranking. See the <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
    </p>
    <h2>Updating the archive</h2><p>
      Product availability, formulations, guidance and evidence change. Each page carries a
      last-reviewed date and a review cadence when ongoing maintenance is needed.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
